Credit, then, to the bold Brussels curators, who are staging the first Zurbar√°n exhibition outside Spain in 27 years. Aptly, the display is in almost complete darkness, and in the case of 1635‚Äôs Christ on the Cross, the result is stunning. In a break with tradition, the Crucifixion is no longer a crowded, mob scene, but a solitary one ‚Äì depicted with enough naturalism to convince the praying believer that Christ has appeared before his eyes.


